== Genealogy == According to the ''Nihon Shoki,'' Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto is the grandson of Emperor Kaika. His father is identified as {{ill|Hikoiimasu no Mikoto|ja|彦坐王|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a prince of Emperor Kaika, although some sources name {{ill|Hikoyumusumi no Mikoto|ja|彦湯産隅命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, another son of Emperor Kaika, as his father.{{Sfn|丹波道主命（古代氏族）|2010th year |p=426}}
The ''Kojiki'' provides additional details, naming Hikoiimasu no Mikoto as his father and Okina no Mizuori-hime (息長水依比売娘), the daughter of Kuninotokotachi no Mikoto, as his mother. The ''Kojiki'' also lists his siblings, including Mizunohowaka no Mikoto (ancestor of the {{ill|Ankoku clans of Shiga|ja|近江安直|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) and Kamiookine no Mikoto (ancestor of the Mino Kuni clans).
=== Children === The ''Nihon Shoki'' and ''Kojiki'' list several wives and children of Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto, including: * '''Hihausu-hime''' (氷羽州比売命) – Consort of Emperor Suinin and mother of Emperor Keikō. * '''Madonohime''' (真砥野媛) – Consort of Emperor Suinin. * '''Chōtei Wakamiya no Mikoto''' (朝廷別王) – Ancestor of the {{ill|Hokuni clans of Mikawa|ja|三川穂国造|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Historical Accounts == In the ''Nihon Shoki,'' Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto was sent to Tanba Province in the 10th year of Emperor Sujin’s reign as one of the Four Commanders of the Four Roads. Alongside other commanders such as {{ill|Ōhiko no Mikoto|ja|大彦命|1=Ōhiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Takeshi Uchino Sukune|ja|武渟川別|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Kibitsuhiko no Mikoto|ja|吉備津彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, he was instrumental in pacifying the region.{{Sfn|丹波道主命（古代氏族）|2010th year |p=426}}
The ''Kojiki,'' however, attributes the expedition to his father, Hikoiimasu no Mikoto, and offers no further details about his activities.
== Burial == Although the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft}} has not designated an official burial site for Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto, the {{ill|Kumobe Kofun|ja|雲部車塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Sasayama, Hyōgo|ja|丹波篠山市|qq=draft|qq=draft}} is traditionally associated with him. This keyhole-shaped tomb, the largest in the Tanba region, is about 140 meters long.{{Sfn|事典陵墓参考地|2005th year |p=49}}
== Legends == The {{ill|Kamitani-Tachi-no-Miya|ja|神谷太刀宮神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Kyōtango|ja|京丹後市|qq=draft|qq=draft}} enshrines Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto as its deity. According to legend, he wielded a sacred sword called "Kunimi no Ken," which gave rise to place names such as "Kunimi" and "Kumihama."{{Sfn|京丹後市観光協会|2005th year }}
== References == {{Reflist}} == See Also == * {{ill|Four Commanders of the Four Roads|ja|四道将軍|1=Shidō Shōgun|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
