The ''Kojiki'' provides additional details, naming Hikoiimasu no Mikoto as his father and Okina no Mizuori-hime (息長水依比売娘), the daughter of Kuninotokotachi no Mikoto, as his mother. The ''Kojiki'' also lists his siblings, including Mizunohowaka no Mikoto (ancestor of the {{ill|Ankoku clans of Shiga|ja|近江安直|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ankoku clans of Shiga|qq=}}) and Kamiookine no Mikoto (ancestor of the Mino Kuni clans).
=== Children === The ''Nihon Shoki'' and ''Kojiki'' list several wives and children of Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto, including: * '''Hihausu-hime''' (氷羽州比売命) – Consort of Emperor Suinin and mother of Emperor Keikō. * '''Madonohime''' (真砥野媛) – Consort of Emperor Suinin. * '''Chōtei Wakamiya no Mikoto''' (朝廷別王) – Ancestor of the {{ill|Hokuni clans of Mikawa|ja|三川穂国造|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hokuni clans of Mikawa|qq=}}.
== Historical Accounts == In the ''Nihon Shoki,'' Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto was sent to Tanba Province in the 10th year of Emperor Sujin’s reign as one of the Four Commanders of the Four Roads. Alongside other commanders such as {{ill|Ōhiko no Mikoto|ja|大彦命|1=Ōhiko-no-Mikoto|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōhiko no Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōhiko-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, {{ill|Takeshi Uchino Sukune|ja|武渟川別|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeshi Uchino Sukune|qq=}}, and {{ill|Kibitsuhiko no Mikoto|ja|吉備津彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kibitsuhiko no Mikoto|qq=}}, he was instrumental in pacifying the region.{{Sfn|丹波道主命（古代氏族）|2010th year |p=426}}
The ''Kojiki,'' however, attributes the expedition to his father, Hikoiimasu no Mikoto, and offers no further details about his activities.
== Burial == Although the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Household Agency|qq=}} has not designated an official burial site for Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto, the {{ill|Kumobe Kofun|ja|雲部車塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumobe Kofun|qq=}} in {{ill|Sasayama, Hyōgo|ja|丹波篠山市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasayama, Hyōgo|qq=}} is traditionally associated with him. This keyhole-shaped tomb, the largest in the Tanba region, is about 140 meters long.{{Sfn|事典陵墓参考地|2005th year |p=49}}
== Legends == The {{ill|Kamitani-Tachi-no-Miya|ja|神谷太刀宮神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitani-Tachi-no-Miya|qq=}} in {{ill|Kyōtango|ja|京丹後市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōtango|qq=}} enshrines Tanba Michinushi no Mikoto as its deity. According to legend, he wielded a sacred sword called "Kunimi no Ken," which gave rise to place names such as "Kunimi" and "Kumihama."{{Sfn|京丹後市観光協会|2005th year }}
